### Describe the bug

In our application we're seeing a 6-8ms delay before the first line of our business logic code is called in OTEL spans:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/26604994/228048340-e902c6b2-9d30-46a3-bd02-ab3b6b7fa3f6.png)

On a fresh Quarkus app, with the below code, I can see about a 1.5-2.0ms delay before `hello()` is called:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/26604994/228048603-e9f5c95c-8be9-4427-9f9f-ffe47647b4be.png)

Is there any way to debug/get visibility into what is happening in the "dead space" before user code is invoked?
Thank you ðŸ™ 

```java
@Path("/hello")
public class GreetingResource {

    @Inject
    Tracer tracer;

    @GET
    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_PLAIN)
    public String hello() {
        return withSpan("hello", tracer, span -> {
            span.setAttribute("hello", "world");
            return withSpan("goodbye", tracer, span2 -> {
                span2.setAttribute("goodbye", "world");
                return "hello";
            });
        });
    }

    private static <T> T withSpan(String name, Tracer tracer, Function<Span, T> function) {
        Span span = tracer.spanBuilder(name).startSpan();
        try (Scope scope = span.makeCurrent()) {
            return function.apply(span);
        } finally {
            span.end();
        }
    }
}
```


